### 4.{{ loop.index }}. {{ action.name }}

| Field | Detail |
|---|---|
| Severity | CRITICAL |
| Regulation | {{ action.regulation }} |
| Owner | {{ action.owner }} |
| Deadline | {{ action.deadline }} |

**Current Gap:** This critical compliance item is not currently satisfied.

**What To Do:**
{{ action.description }}

**Implementation Steps:**
{% if "shadow" in action.name | lower %}
1. Conduct an anonymous staff survey to identify unapproved AI tool usage
2. Review network logs and browser histories for AI tool access patterns
3. Implement web filtering to block known unapproved AI services
4. Establish a formal AI tool request and approval process
5. Communicate the Shadow AI policy to all staff with amnesty period
6. Deploy endpoint monitoring for ongoing detection
{% elif "cross-border" in action.name | lower or "DPA" in action.name | lower or "vendor" in action.name | lower %}
1. Inventory all AI tools that process data overseas
2. Contact each vendor to request their standard DPA
3. Review DPA terms with legal counsel — ensure APP 8 compliance
4. Execute DPAs with all overseas AI tool vendors
5. Document data flow maps showing what data goes where
6. Establish quarterly vendor review process
{% elif "acceptable use" in action.name | lower %}
1. Use this tool to generate the AI Acceptable Use Policy
2. Review the generated policy with legal counsel and management
3. Customise any sections requiring organisation-specific detail
4. Get formal management sign-off
5. Distribute to all staff with mandatory acknowledgement
6. Schedule training on the new policy
{% elif "POLA" in action.name | lower or "automated" in action.name | lower or "transparent" in action.name | lower %}
1. Inventory all automated decision systems currently in use
2. For each system, document: inputs, logic, outputs, and affected individuals
3. Draft transparency notices explaining automated decision-making
4. Update the privacy policy to include automated decision disclosures
5. Implement a human review mechanism for each automated decision type
6. Test the disclosure and review process before the December 2026 deadline
{% elif "ACL" in action.name | lower or "content" in action.name | lower or "consumer" in action.name | lower %}
1. Identify all AI-generated customer-facing content workflows
2. Implement mandatory human review checkpoints before publication
3. Create a review checklist covering accuracy, completeness, and compliance
4. Train content teams on ACL obligations (s18 strict liability)
5. Establish an audit trail for reviewed content
6. Conduct monthly spot-checks of published AI-generated content
{% elif "human oversight" in action.name | lower %}
1. Identify all AI-assisted decision processes affecting individuals
2. Document the current level of human involvement in each process
3. Implement mandatory human review before decisions are finalised
4. Create escalation pathways for disputed AI-assisted decisions
5. Train decision-makers on their review responsibilities
6. Establish audit logging for all AI-assisted decisions
{% else %}
1. Assess the current state against the specific requirement
2. Identify resources and approvals needed to address the gap
3. Implement the required controls, policies, or processes
4. Document evidence of compliance
5. Communicate changes to affected stakeholders
6. Schedule ongoing monitoring to maintain compliance
{% endif %}

